This project depends on a database connection.

-------- STEP 1 --------
	The database must have a table with the following structure (table name can change):

	CREATE TABLE `log` (
	  `rowNum` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
	  `date` varchar(10) NOT NULL,
	  `calories` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
	  `exercise` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
	  `notes` text NOT NULL,
	  `temp` text NOT NULL
	) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

-------- STEP 2 --------
	Rename Config-TEMPLATE.php to Config.php and input your mysql connection variables
	- hostname
	- username
	- password
	- database
	- userTable ('user' by default)
	- logTable ('log' by default)
